text: Star Building is a historic commercial building located at Terre Haute, Vigo County, Indiana. It was built in 1912, and is a four-story, Chicago school style brick building. It features limestone and terra cotta detailing and a pressed metal decorative cornice. The building was built to house the Terra Haute Star newspaper.
